Our family has been using Heather's Home Cleaning for several months now and it has been a wonderful experience.  Isabel cleans our home on a biweekly basis.  She is such a sweet person, always polite, punctual, and does an immaculate job.  At the beginning of every visit she checks in with me to see if I have any specific requests for that day's cleaning.  I have pretty high standards for house cleaning and I have found my expectations met and exceeded every time.  Besides the large tasks, she pays attention to the details: corners are dusted, mildew in the cracks of plumbing fixtures are cleaned, the grills on the stove top are soaked and washed, she even takes time to vacuum the sofa and get those crumbs that always get left behind by my kids.  My house is left sparkling.</Review>

(Translated by Google) Three friends went, and we made an unforgettable trip thanks to Purunsol Guesthouse.
I made a reservation as a female dormitory, but he upgraded our room because the general room was open for a few days, and the La trip plan was not salty, but he made a plan for the day of entering, and he gave us plenty of towels to use.
There were 2 toilets, and considering the space used by several people, I stayed for 4 days and there was no big inconvenience.
Most of all, the atmosphere of having a drink between people staying at the hostel at night was good, and thanks to Uncle Thomas, who always takes care of our safety even on desert tours, we have been traveling with fun~
If you like to hang out with people and want to make a little special trip, we recommend Purunsol Guesthouse~~!!

(Translated by Google) This is the first guest house where I traveled alone and stayed there for 7 days! I was worried that a woman was traveling alone, so I read a lot of reviews and made a decision after meticulous searching! It was a place that made me meet the best relationships and comfortable rooms on a trip where everything was new and unfamiliar!

Every morning, I greeted him with Uncle Paul, had breakfast, listened to advice, and ended up having a light beer with Uncle Thomas at night after having fun all day! My uncles were so friendly that I was able to have a great time with all of the people who were there!

But it was the Joshua Desert Tour that made this guest house so unforgettable for me. It was really like a family trip thanks to my uncle's desire to feel the Joshua Desert with my whole body and share the beautiful scenery, not the tour that travel agencies do!
As soon as I got out of the car, the stars pouring over my head, the endless desert, cactus and Joshua Tree that calmed my mind! The pork belly and ramen my uncle gave me was really the best!!!

This trip was one of the best trips in my youth life trip. Part of that good memory, Purunsol Guesthouse! Thank you for making such great memories! I'll see you again when I go to LA soon!! hehe

(Translated by Google) It was a really happy trip every moment.
As I stayed in Purunsol from 11/16 to 11/21, I think I could feel the impact of accommodation on my trip once again.

1. Desert Tour

I slept for 2-3 hours as soon as I arrived on the 16th, and even though I departed immediately after being tired, I never felt tired for a moment until the desert tour was over the next morning. Even the sunrise I watched while it was getting bright was really perfect... Seeing it separately, my uncle took a pretty picture, and after watching the sunrise, the pork belly burned warmly and grilled right in the fire in the desert is really...üëèüèª Please make sure to visit all of them. I hope I can't express everything in writing, but it was more than I imaginedüò≠üíï

2. Accommodation

I used a dormitory for two with two friends, but it was nice to have a queen bed and a bunk bed so I could choose the bed I wanted to use and relax!
While traveling in various countries, I know how important it is to relieve fatigue at the accommodation when you come to the accommodation after a full day trip, but this trip has a tight schedule every day, and when you come to the accommodation, you can relax comfortably, so I was able to digest the schedule for the next day without fatigue.
During the desert tour, the riders of the same desert tour stayed together all day and became friends. After that, thanks to my uncle, I had a lot of fun talking with everyone who stayed in the guesthouse every night after a schedule.
Even if we eat dinner and drink together at a guest house, this comfortable and fun atmosphere lasts every day, but it's not easy, but it was always nice that my uncle made it all together without any awkwardness at all!!!
It was every day that the desert tour riders became more sticky with each other and were so good even with those who didn't go together...üíï

3. Facilities

The female dormitory is located on the first floor, so it would be more comfortable when using the shower, toilet and dryer inside the dormitory!
We had a double room on the second floor, so it was on the same floor as a male dormitory, but there was no inconvenience in using the shower and toilet at all. I went to several Korean guesthouses and guest houses, but shampoo, soap, cleansing foam, especially body wash!! There are many places that are not there, but it is always arranged so I used it without worry. La felt dry, so I think it would be nice to take extra hair essence or treatment!
The dryer is located inside the shower on the first floor and next to the washbasin in front of the bathroom on the second floor.
There are many people who offer breakfast as short as 8:00-9:00, but you can use it in abundance from 7:30 to 10:30. You can prepare bananas, bread, etc. before or after meal time, or put it on the table anytime. I was able to eat comfortably when I woke up hahaha

4.Others
It was a desert tour, a trip that took only a large frame except for Disneyland tickets, but when I arrived and checked in, my uncle also recommended itinerary and what day would be more advantageous when I go to where! He gave me some tips, so I watched the Disney fireworks that I couldn't see haha
I arrived in Korea yesterday and it was already a good place to want to go again.
Please come and take a desert tour and have a beer at night and have fun!!
Even those who are worried about being noisy because they drink beer every night don't have to worry at all. Those who are tired from eating and drinking after closing all the doors in the living room are no problem when sleeping first!! Originally, I slept at 11 o'clock when I went on a trip, too, so I got to play without sleeping here, but üòÇ

Thank you so much for your uncle, I'm going well, I'll definitely come back with 316th !!Thank youüíï

<Review>It wasn't bad, but not the greatest.

PROS:
Music was eclectic, truly a mix and it was fun.

Ambiance was cool, the outdoor firepits and  VIP sections looked great.

We got in for free since the hotel gave us free entrance cards.

Women's bathroom was clean and attended to by a nice lady. Slight Con: only 4 stalls.

CONS:
It was so packed, you could barely move. Honestly, didnt seem safe. A few bouncers were a little abrupt in telling us to move out of the way since we were blocking the walkway, but it felt like we just had to keep going and wedge ourselves somewhere.

There was no AC where the most people were, which was the dance floor. If there was it was weak.

It's on the second floor, up a lot of stairs, which I don't understand why clubs continue to do this to very drunk people, some of which are in heels. Obviously not something they can change or improve, but just be warned.

Facts:
Not sure if thus fluctuates, but VIP booths, we were told were $400. For a bottle of booze and the right to sit.< /Review><rate>3<//rate><Time>1565546130486</Time></record></dataset><record>

< Review>
Have been to the Mix many times. It is the best place to go in Sacramento.  Recently went on a Thursday for Happy Hour. We had such a great time.  Loved it so much we went back the next night for 'Happy Hearts Day.' I always have fun when I go on Saturdays but hadn't been on a Friday. Had an amazing time!  The service was excellent starting from the door guys to the bartenders all the way up to management. The food is delicious and menu offers healthy and light options. The music was perfect; good variety for a wide age range to enjoy. The decor is elegant but still cozy during HH and fun and exciting during club hours. I will def be returning to the Mix.< /Review>

<Rating>5< /Rating>< text>
I love this classic diner. The outside is folksy with an awning; the  interior is old-school but very clean. As of April 2021, they've reopened their indoor dining with limited, safe-distance seating.

My 1/3 lb Cheddar cheeseburger was perfectly cooked (m), my fries hot and crispy, and the coffee (decaf for evening) was delicious.  I love that Ole's offers a choice of American, Swiss, Jack, or Cheddar instead of just the usual American cheese. My DH had a very good patty melt - although they mistakenly gave him American instead of Cheddar cheese. He didn't bother to send it back because that's hardly something to toss out a perfectly good sandwich over. Their salads have perky dark-green "leaf" lettuce, beets, and sunflower seeds.<//text>

< Text>
One of the best breakfasts in the East Bay. My favorite is the pecan waffle, top it with a mound of fruit and everyone will stare with jealousy at the glorious creation. A true east bay gem will always have Portuguese sausage on the menu as well so I always have to order some Lingui√ßa every time I go.  This is the type of place everyone can agree on, my parents love it. It‚Äôs stood the test of time since opening in 1927. When dine-in is open you can skip the line and sit at the counter which is open seating, which is my fave cause I like watching people cook. Friendly and fast service. You can also order their waffle mix from the website, it makes a great gift!< /Text>

<Response>None</Response>< text>
Old school diner with traditional American fare.
Breakfast can be ordered all day.
Prices are great considering how much food is offered.

For example, I ordered the Liver and Onions. Comes with a choice of a soup or salad. Also a side of mashed potatoes or rice. And then some mixed cooked vegetables. It was a lot of food.

Didn‚Äôt have an appetite for veggies, so I only ate the liver, saut√©ed onions and the rice.

Felt like the onions were either over cooked or the grill needed to be cleaned. Too many of the onions tasted charred and greasy.

The liver had a similar taste. Like it had been cooked on a grill that had burnt remnants of other food.

Rice was fine.

With the above considered, I wouldn‚Äôt order the liver and onions again, but I would definitely go back to try something else on the menu.

As of April 2021, dining in is available during COVID, but seating is spaced out with social distancing in mind.

The waitresses service was okay. No complaints.

Final score, 4.2 out of 5, which equates to an 84 out of 100.

Not too shabby.<//text>

< userid>
110515628787338311455< /userid>
<Name>Bill Collins<//Name><time>1614478386413</time>< rate>
5</rate>
< review>
This restaurant is fantastic!!!  Every time I eat here, I get that comfortable feeling I always get in a good old-fashioned diner!!!

I read a few other comments about how crowded it was on odd days, like Tuesday mornings, and it was the same for us too.  A very unusual weekday morning, and "locals" not businessmen on meetings were hanging out there!!!  Very well known and loved.

They have all the common breakfast fodder, delicious omelettes, egg and waffles, bacon, delicious and unusual Southern offerings, like grits and biscuits and gravy, and many fruit and vegetarian type offerings too.

This place was so good, I brought my mother and family here for an after graduation celebration, I think for my daughter's 5th grade graduation.  It has been packed, virtually every single time we visit.

I have yet to try any of their desserts, like pie. I think I had chocolate cake and ice-cream at least once, but I"m not a big fan of cake, so it was just so-so.  I'm sure most would enjoy it!!

Last time I was in, I saw around 6 Alameda High students sidle up to the counter top, and all were treated the same as any other customer, which I appreciated seeing.

RECOMMENDED!!!</review>

< text>
Unfortunately, something drastic has changed here in past several years.
It was really disappointing, since it used to be quite good and worth a half hour drive.
The omelette had a layer of oil on it and everything tasted like it was from Sysco (restaurant distributor). The pecan waffle had the nuts tossed on it after cooking, as though they forgot to add them to batter first. It wouldn't have been too difficult to make it over, if that's the case. If not, wow, what lazy cooking. The OJ didn't seem fresh even though there was an industrial juicer, and it was weak. The coffee? Don't. Just don't.<//text>

< Review>
My guy and I enjoyed a short get-a-way to the Bay area. So of course before flying out Sunday morning to Ontario we stopped by Ollie's Waffel Shop in Alameda for breakfast. What a Great place to eat while following Covid-10 precautions. The food was deLiCious. I had the Pancake combo whereby the pancakes were very soft, fluffy and melt in your mouth. The red potatoes and Hot Chocolate was an added bonus. My guy enjoyed his Omelet with hashbrowns. The customer service was excellent and attentive. Ollie's is a must visit anytime im in the Oakland area.</Review>

j spain Greene<//username>
< date>
1550693704844< /date>
< Rate>
5<//Rate>
< text>
We adored this old diner that hops with activity.  The staff is fantastic - fast and efficient, a well-oiled professional diner machine.
The menu is large - everyone will find something they want for every meal.  The specialty is breakfast, obviously waffles are heavy on the menu and live up to the diner hype.  You will pay a little extra for fresh fruit - but I think it's a nice option.  They list the fruits available that day on a sign at the front door.
Ole's has great sweet breakfasts - I loved the French Toast especially and there were a lot of orders of it going out.  But they also have plenty of savoury food - breakfast meats, eggs.
If you are a diner fan, Ole's is definitely worth a stop!  If you're not into diners, you will still find a consistent meal.<//text>

< Review>
Great cafe to go to start your day with a delicious breakfast! Has a wonderful variety of egg/combo dishes, omelettes, French toast & waffles of course! They also serve lunch & dinner from viewing their menu (you can see menu on-line on their website). Conveniently located just minutes down the street from the Alameda Shopping Center on Park Street in Alameda! There's street parking so you may have to park near by if you don't luck out to nab a parking spot in or near the front! Worth going there & comparable to any other restaurant in price & good portion of food!</Review>

< Text>
Friendly and high quality customer service. I had coffee and pancakes. I could have sipped the coffee all day but the pancakes were not great. It could have been a one-off thing, but while they were the right level of moist and fluffy, they fell apart at the slightest movement, making it pretty difficult to get from the plate to my mouth. And once syrup was involved, forget it - half the pancake stayed on the plate in a crumbly, syrupy mixture. I'll probably give it another chance just in case it was a fluke, because the rest of the dining experience was exactly what you want in a diner.< /Text>

<user>101304777884991379041</user><Response>None< /Response><rating>4<//rating>< review>
I give 4 stars only because a 5 star restaurant is upscale. As far as the food is concerned, it's five stars, in my opinion. It's cooked in front of you, it tastes great, it's cooked, the way you like it, the first time. I'm very critical about the food that I consider "good", because I can cook myself. I have had no issues, at all, here. If you want a good meal, served fairly quickly, this is your place. Their service is friendly, and accommodating, and I love the fact that I see a little off all races eating here. That's always a sign of good food being served. This is my 2nd time here, and I'll definitely be back.< /review>

<review>food and service here was great! After doing a search on  Check Please! (A bay area food talk show),  my partner found tnis place he remembered from 6 years ago. We. < user>
115623616059859182708<//user>
< username>
Jeff<//username>
< date>
1473396975235</date>
<rate>4< /rate><review>The All-American Diner...
If you've spent anytime on the East Coast the concept of a diner isn't something you need to explain. Here on the West Coast it's more along the lines of a Coffee Shop. Ole's Waffle Shop is both. It's a place that serves breakfast, and an amazing breakfast at that, all day. Everything on the breakfast menu is wonderful, from the hash browns to the waffles. But the also serve classic diner fare as well, open turkey face sandwiches, french fries, fried chicken along with homemade soup and chili. The best way to describe the place is it's everything Denny's wants to be, just a whole lot better.</review><Pics>None</Pics>< resp>

<gmap_id>0x808f8695ecc3bf97:0x8fd7faf4af9ea344<//gmap_id>< Date>
1541050387875<//Date>
< review>
We lived in Alameda for almost 25 yrs and used to take our inlaws to Ole's and Tillie's. Tillie's is long gone, but Ole's is still going strong--and is better now than it ever was. Delicious, high grade thick-slice bacon, crispy and wonderful, old fashion waffle iron waffles. And for an extra $2.50 you can buy an individual bottle of pure maple syrup if you like and refuse the high fructose phony stuff. The service is comfy, kind, and friendly as an old pair of favorite tennis shoes. The menu offers special omelettes every day it seems. But we go to Ole's for the waffles! Recommended.</review>

< Review>
Went to a waffle shop and ordered french toast; did I break any rules?  Their french toast was seriously delicious and the syrup they provide is a good pairing.  I was able to try some of their biscuits and gravy too, not too bad, but not too impressive either.  I did not get the pleasure to try a waffle, however everyone in our group said they were amazing.  And if they are as good as the french toast, then I 100% will order the waffles next time.
Only docking 1 star because we were sat in the back section.  You had to walk through the kitchen to get to the table.  It was loud and smelled like cleaning solution mixed with whatever food they were making.</Review>

<user>112718526373847173096< /user><user_name>Mike Criddle</user_name>< time>
1415500880160<//time>
<Rate>5<//Rate>< Review>
I've eaten at Ole's twice now : both times the service has been excellent with very friendly outgoing staff/servers. Most importantly , this is a WAFFLE shop , and the waffles are terrific. The fresh orange juice is squeezed right before your eyes in a wonderful old juicer / dispenser...1940's or 50's vintage...so cool and delicious....Lots of waffle places are popular nowadays and Belgians "are all the craze" but Ole's are the best, crisp and light , just the way I like em!</Review>

<Rating>4< /Rating>< Text>
Ole's Waffle Shop has been around a long time, and there's a reason why. This is my favorite breakfast place in Alameda. They have many great things on the menu, and it's all delicious, but as their namesake would suggest, the waffles are wonderful. That is my favorite breakfast item here. They also serve many other kinds of food though and are open all day. I've eaten here for dinner and it's just as good. You feel like you're having a nice meal at home.<//Text>

<Time>1515089672830</Time>< rating>
5</rating>
< Text>
Great atmosphere and service at this cute traditional diner. I'd take out of town visitors here just for the experience. Dropped in around 3ish for a snack so there were plenty of available tables. About $18 for waffles and a side of 4 link sausages and a cup of coffee. The waffles were freshly made, light and crispy - we loved them but don't expect to feel full. It's a little pricey just for waffles but for a park street location it's to be expected. The moving minuture carousels and Christmas  fairground scenes in the window were a nice touch as well.</Text>

< review>
Germ-a-phobes, and hypochondriacs beware. This place puts forth a five star effort but their cleanliness leaves much to be desired. While there I watched the chef cough on his arm, and handle raw meat with his bare hands without washing before handling other food items. Crums and dirt that accumulated on the prep counter was haphazardly flung to the floor as well as into the food that was stacked on top of each other waiting to be served. The toast I ordered with my meal was soaked with drippings from the food that had been stacked on top of it as it sat waiting to be served to me. The food was no frills as advertised and served in hearty portions (this is a good thing). Although extremely busy, the staff remained pleasant to the customers. I witnessed a server settle a monetary dispute with a customer by paying the difference out of her own pocket! Even after the customer left, the server continued to affirm that she did not mind doing it. BUT... at times, (more than what I deem acceptable) the staff could be heard using inappropriate language in their personal discussions that occurred in front of the customers. Picture a classier Waffle House.< /review>

0x808f8695ecc3bf97:0x8fd7faf4af9ea344< /gmap_id>
</record></dataset><record>
< text>
Arrived on Saturday morning and there was quite a line at the door, but it goes by quickly.

I ordered the waffle combo with 1 scrambled egg and upgraded to chicken apple sausage (got chicken garlic instead). Bf ordered potato pancake special with sausage and eggs, and also ordered a side of hash browns.

Tried a sip of the fresh squeezed orange juice. Eh, it's ok. I wish it was served cold. But again, I'm biased when it comes to good oj (Florida girl here ;))

Food was decent. Nothing bad, but nothing spectacular. The waffle was good! But I found the rest to be standard. Hash browns had no flavor though.

Service is quick, so I can see how they turn tables so fast.

Worth giving it a try, but I don't think it's be my first option to go to for breakfast in Alameda.< /text>

<userid>102669212346157724265</userid>< name>
Kristen Burgess</name>
<time>1510625738415</time>< rating>
4<//rating>
<Text>I really liked this place for having a no BS attitude and being a classic American diner. From my experience don't expect the wait staff to have much time for you to explain all your food allergies. Basically, think Ron Swanson.

We went on a Sunday at 12:30ish pm. We waited outside for about 15 minutes and were seated at a 2 top. We got coffee and a fresh squeezed oj. The coffee is weak--probably Farm Bros or something, but the oj was so dang good. I got the pecan waffle with eggs, the husband got the Spanish omelet with hash browns and a biscuit. They were both super tasty. We were stuffed afterwards and agreed we'll be making Ole's a normal stop for hangover afternoons.<//Text>< pics>
None<//pics>

<Rate>2< /Rate>< Text>
I just moved to the East Bay, and have been really excited to try some new restaurants. But it seems like everytime I go to Alameda to eat, I'm kind of left disappointed. The day after I moved to Oakland, I looked for a breakfast spot to eat at with some friends. Decided to go with this place, and realized that was a bad move. The place gets surprisingly packed. Is it for good reason? No.  I shared a lot of dishes with my friends, only to find out that the food is just okay. Seating is not worthy of being filled up the way it does. It seems like a local spot. But I've had a lot of great local breakfast spots from different places, and this place is so mediocre. And you would think that their waffles would at least stand out? But they don't. Will definitely not be coming back here. Oh and the waiters and waitresses seem so unhappy. It's not like an unhappy and untasty place.</Text>
